0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aRising Up traces the history and international context of living wage movements across Canada. This compassionate and astute collection of essays shines a light on alternatives to a neoliberalized labour market, examining union- and community-based approaches to labour organizing, migrant labour, and media (mis)representations, among other key topics. Canada has one of the highest rates of low-wage work among advanced industrial economies. In a labour market characterized by the ongoing fallout from COVID-19, deepening income inequality, job instability, and diluted union representation, the living wage movement offers a response and solutions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aLabor marketzCanada. 0aLiving wage movementzCanada. 0aWageszCanada. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Process / Political Advocacy.2bisacsh1 aBauder, Harald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEvans, Bryan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEvans, Bryan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFanelli, Carlo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFanelli, Carlo, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFerdosi, Mohammad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoutor, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHammond, Kendall, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHannan, Charity-Ann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHudson, Carol-Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnston, Mary-Dan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabula